               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-933" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-933" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-933" type="surname" value="DYER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-933" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>DANIEL DYER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to William Sumshon Hayes, a general dealer, in Farringdon-street. Between six and seven o'clock in the even<lb></lb>ing of the 9th of April, I was in the shop, lighting the gas—I saw the prisoner take this pair of trowsers from a board in the doorway, and run up Farringdon-market—I pursued him, and told a policeman, who also pursued—I saw him drop the trowsers in Farringdon market—I picked them up—they are Mr. Hayes' property—the policeman pursued the prisoner—I had seen him about the door previously—as I came out I once saw him snatch his hand away, aud walk on as far as Stonecutter-street—he then came back again, but some one was at the door, and he made no attempt</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184504070171"></xptr>
               <p>then, but the third time he took them—I am sure he is the person I pursued.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Had you seen my face? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—about an hour before the trowsers were taken.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-934" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-934" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-934" type="surname" value="BARNES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-934" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BARNES</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City police-constable, No.</hi> 273.) I saw persons running, and followed—the prisoner was pointed out to me by some boys who were pursuing him, and I took him into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I know nothing about it; I had been drinking all the afternoon at a public-house; I went up a yard, and as I came down the policeman took me.</p>
